; byte) BGR555 palette. Frame order: 12 directions (pitch*4+turn) x 2 propeller
; states (frames 0-11 = prop A, 12-23 = prop B). Each 512-byte frame is 4
; blocks of 128 bytes; each block is one tile-row of 4 contiguous 8x8 4bpp
; tiles (left to right). The rail uploads the 4 blocks of a frame to VRAM
; tile-rows 16 apart (the hardware 32x32 OBJ contract) and uses the straight-
; facing prop-A/prop-B pair (frames 0 and 12) for the animated idle.
; =============================================================================

